documentation.value: None interrupts mask

Chirp sequence start interupt. - Positive edge: Clock cycle after chirp start trigger. - Negative edge: End of dwell time of first chirp in sequence. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)

Chirp sequence end interupt. - Positive edge: Start of reset time of last chirp in sequence. - Negative edge: Unclear from documentation for the case of single chirp sequence triggering. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)
Chirp start interupt. - Positive edge: Start of dwell time of each chirp. - Negative edge: End of dwell time of each chirp. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)

Chirp start interupt. - Positive edge: End of reset time of each chirp. - Negative edge: End of dwell time of next chirp. For last chirp, start of dwell time of first chirp in next chirp sequence. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)

Acquisition start interupt. - Positive edge: Start of acquisition time of each chirp. - Negative edge: End of dwell time of next chirp. For last chirp, start of dwell time of first chirp in next chirp sequence. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)

Acquisition end interupt. - Positive edge: End of acquisition time of each chirp. - Negative edge: End of dwell time of next chirp. For last chirp, start of dwell time of first chirp in next chirp sequence. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)
Ramp start interupt. - Positive edge: Start of settle time of each chirp. - Negative edge: End of acquisition time. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)

DC power on start interupt. - Positive edge: Clock cycle after chirp start trigger. - Negative edge: End of dwell time of first chirp in next chirp sequence. (Only applies whens interrupts are configured as level with HW auto-clear)

\brief This function initializes the TE SW Unit \details This function initializes the TE SW Unit. It - Enables timing engine It configures the following parameters with SW constants: - Enable RXBIST signals towards Packer/RXBIST IP - Configure dynamic power control - Enable Tx PR Calibration - Configure TE interrupts towards NVIC - DC Power on Time - Safety monitoring activation timing - TX/RX power on timing - Rx filter enable/reset timing - Fast enable pulse width & de-assertion delays - Dynamic power disable delay per chirp and for chirp sequence (to keep IPs enabled for BIST) This function is called by the rfeInit SW Unit and shall be the first TE function to be called. \pre NIL \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function sets the TE chirp profile parameters. \details This function sets the TE chirp profile parameters for a selected profile. This function is called by rfeSwCfgMngr at (re-)configuration. \pre NIL \param [in] chirpProfileIndex - Chirp profile index to program \param [in] pTeChirpProfile - Pointer to chirp profile config structure, with the values to set \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function sets the TE chirp deactivation time. \details This function is called by rfeSwCfgMngr at (re-)configuration. \pre NIL \param [in] deactivationTimeTicks - The chirp deactivation time \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function sets the chirp profile sequence. \details This function is called by rfeSwCfgMngr at (re-)configuration. \pre NIL \param [in] chirpCount - Number of chirps to start Maximum length is #RFE_CHIRP_PROFILE_SEQUENCE_LENGTH_MAX \param [in] profileSequencingMode - Selects how chirp profiles are sequenced: Single profile / round-robin or as defined by chirp profile list Maximum length is #RFE_CHIRP_PROFILE_SEQUENCE_LENGTH_MAX. The chirp profile list mode has to been selected when using dynamic programming. \param [in] pChirpProfileList - Array of chirp profile indices. Maximum length is #RFE_CHIRP_PROFILE_SEQUENCE_LENGTH_MAX. Only the first \p chirpProfileSequenceLength entries are considered. Only applicable when profile sequencing mode is set to chirp profile list, a null pointer can be given otherwise. \param [in] chirpProfileListLength - Length of chirp profile sequence before proceeding to the next entry in the chirp profile sequence. Only applicable when profile sequencing mode is set to chirp profile list. * \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function sets the chirp active signal config. \details This function is called by rfeSwCfgMngr at (re-)configuration. \pre NIL \param [in] chirpActiveSignalConfig - Configures the signal that indicates when a chirp (sequence) is active. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function programs the rfe_te_trigger select mux and the GPIO_6_oe and GPIO_7_oe signals to enable external chirpstart triggers \details The select argument is written in the 5 bit field [0..4] to select a MUX input Use defines for rfeHwTe_externalChirpStartTriggerSource_t to select the correct input GPIO_6_oe and GPIO_7_oe are enabled if GPIO_6 or GPIO_7 is selected by the select argument \pre NIL \param [in] select - the MUX input to select, use defines for rfeHwTe_externalChirpStartTriggerSource_t [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function sets the resets moment of the monitor counters. \details This function sets the resets moment of the rx saturation and / or pdc clipping counters. This function is called by rfeSwCfgMngr. \pre NIL \param [in] resetRxSaturationCountEveryChirpSequence - Selection of Rx saturation counters to be reset at the beginning of every chirp sequence. Resets I & Q counters of both Rx stages. \param [in] resetPdcClippingCountEveryChirpSequence - If true all PDC clipping counters will be reset at the beginning of every chirp sequence. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function resets selected monitors counters. \details This function resets selected rx saturation and / or pdc clipping counts. This function is called by rfeSwMainFsm \pre NIL \param [in] rxSaturationCountSelect - Selection of Rx saturation counters to be reset immediately. Resets I & Q counters of both Rx stages. \param [in] pdcClippingCounts - If true all PDC clipping counters will be reset immediately. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function start the Tx phase rotation calibration. \details This function start the Tx phase rotation calibration for selected transmitters. This function is called by the Calibration SW Unit. \pre rfeHwTe_init() must be called. \param [in] txSelect - Selection of transmitter to calibrate. \param [in] timeoutTicks - Timout of calibration in ticks. After timeout ISM will be notified. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function returns the status of Tx phase rotation calibration. \details This function returns the status of the Tx phase rotation calibration. This function is called by the Calibration SW Unit. \pre - rfeHwTe_init() must be called. - rfeHwTe_startTxPhaseRotationCalibration() must be called. - Timeout of rfeHwTe_startTxPhaseRotationCalibration() must have expired. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return rfeHwTe_calibrationStatus_t - Calibration status: success/failure \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief Static inline function to enable TE interrupts \details See #rfeHwTe_interruptBitmask_t for the interrupts description. This function is used by RFE Init SW Unit, to enable TE interrupts required for features like dynamic programming. \pre NIL \param [in] bitmask - Bitmask indicating which interrupts to enable/disable. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function will load a profile across the rfe. \details This function will load a profile across the rfe without triggering a chirp sequence. This function is called by the Calibration SW Unit, Bist SW Unit and via the MainFsm for the continuous wave mode. \pre rfeHwTe_init() must be called. \param [in] chirpProfileIndex - Chirp profile index to load \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return rfeHwTe_txPrCalibrationStatus_t - Calibration status per Tx \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function initializes dynamic programming for the next chirp sequence. \details This function initializes dynamic programming for the next chirp sequence and programs the dynamic registers for the first chirp. This function is called by the MainFsm. This function should be called before starting a chirp sequence. \pre - rfeHwTe_init() must be called. - rfeHwTe_setChirpProfile() must be called (to create dynamic shadow registers) \param [in] pDynamicTables - Pointer to dynamic tables \param [in] dynamicTableIndex - Dynamic table index to be used for next chirp sequence \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function prepares dynamic programming of the next chirp. \details This function prepares dynamic programming of the next chirp to reduce the dynamic programming time as much as possible due to tight timing constraints. It will read the dynamic values for the next chirp from the dynamic table and store it in a shadow registers in RFE M7 DTCM. This function is called by the MainFsm to prepare the dynamic programming for the next-next chirp, when programming the next-chirp is done. This function can be executed during chirp acquisition, it does not interact with the RFE HW. For programming the dynamic registers for the second chirp, this function should be called a.s.a.p after calling rfeHwTe_chirpSequenceStart(), i.e. during the DC power on time. For each other chirps, this function shall be call a.s.a.p. after calling the rfeHwTe_dynamicProgramNextChirp() function. \pre - rfeHwTe_dynamicProgramInit() must be called. - rfeHwTe_chirpSequenceStart() must be called. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function programs the dynamic register for the next chirp. \details It writes the shadow registers in RFE M7 DTCM, that was created by rfeHwTe_dynamicProgramChirpPrepare(), to the TE registers. This function is called by MainFsm a.s.a.p after the profile load moment (start of dwell time) of each chirp. This function must finish before acquisition starts to prevent interference, this is checked and an error will be thrown otherwise. \pre - rfeHwTe_dynamicProgramInit() must be called. - rfeHwTe_chirpSequenceStart() must be called. - rfeHwTe_dynamicProgramNextChirpPrepare() must be called (for every chirp). \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function starts a chirp sequence \details This function starts chirp sequence as configured. This function is called by the MainFsm or by the Bist SW Unit to start Rx Bist chirps. \pre rfeHwTe_init() must be called. \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function powers an IP on (standby to on) or puts in back into standby. \param [in] ip - IP to power on or put to standby \param [in] powerOn - True = power on, False = standby \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL
